        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 19 at 4:08PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 408 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms over Gala, or near Eagle Rock, moving southeast at 15
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Covington...
Eagle Rock...
Oriskany...
Jordan Mines...
Low Moor...
Glen Wilton...
and Gala.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Locally heavy rain will quickly reduce visibility and result in
ponding of water on roadways, standing water in low lying areas, and
minor flooding of creeks, streams, and areas of poor drainage.
Drivers are urged to slow down and use extra caution to avoid
hydroplaning.</instruction>
